The paper deals with the convergence rate of the HITS algorithm, which is commonly used in information retrieval and web search. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. However, the paper also involves analyzing the properties of a graph, which suggests that it could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves mathematical analysis and matrix multiplication, which suggests that it could belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
